Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.49,0:10:03.29,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was hoping there'd be a pattern\Nto the way she's forgetting things.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.12,0:10:06.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I can't quite figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.05,0:10:17.80,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, is there anything common amongst\Nthe relatives that she's forgotten?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.80,0:10:23.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They all live on the other side of the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.68,0:10:25.52,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't see them at the market or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.60,0:10:31.06,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's just forgetting all the things\Nshe doesn't see very often.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.90,0:10:37.82,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, in that case, she should have\Nlong forgotten her husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.29,0:10:51.83,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's getting late. Doesn't look like she's\Ngoing to sleep any time soon though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.33,0:10:53.25,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.59,0:10:56.76,dialogue,,0,0,0,,She says she has a hard time trying to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.05,0:11:05.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she weaves all night long, thinking\Nabout Dad so that she doesn't forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.23,0:11:10.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.31,0:11:13.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she could at least sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.73,0:11:16.40,dialogue,,0,0,0,,waiting would be a bit easier for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.82,0:11:22.11,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A warm wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.41,0:11:24.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the scent of flowers,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.74,0:11:27.16,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}the sound of weaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.04,0:11:34.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Normally, such a night...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.46,0:11:42.72,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}would be a night to fall into a deep, deep slumber.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.15,0:11:57.19,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's finally dozing off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.57,0:12:05.70,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's awake already?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.03,0:12:08.04,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it morning already?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.21,0:12:13.79,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Breakfast, breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.63,0:12:17.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.18,0:12:32.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.48,0:12:38.48,dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Mushi that eats memories?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.02,0:12:41.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's called a Kagedama.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.78,0:12:45.03,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a translucent, black sheet-like Mushi
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.41,0:12:48.87,dialogue,,0,0,0,,that likes to submerge in the shadows of old, tall trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.95,0:12:53.33,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There they wait for people and animals to sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.75,0:12:56.42,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and enter the brains through their ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.63,0:13:00.25,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the hosts become unable to sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.71,0:13:04.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and slowly lose their memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.18,0:13:10.68,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one of those in the cherry tree's shadow?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:12.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.02,0:13:17.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once they consume a certain amount\Nof memories, they multiply internally.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.23,0:13:21.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The duplicates escape from the hosts during\Nthe short time that they're asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.40,0:13:26.24,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those then hide back in the tree's\Nshadow. That's how they multiply.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.95,0:13:31.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally they're frail, and they vanish under sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.29,0:13:36.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But once they're inside, they enter deep into the brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.33,0:13:39.25,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and there's nothing that can be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.59,0:13:42.25,dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there's no way to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.30,0:13:46.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their only known weakness is exposure to light.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.01,0:13:50.51,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's no way to shine light in your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.51,0:13:56.31,dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, there might be a way to protect\Nwhat you don't want to forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.40,0:14:05.03,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's say that the memories in your\Nbrain are sorted into drawers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.95,0:14:11.91,dialogue,,0,0,0,,With ones about dango, your\Ndistant relatives, sneezing...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.70,0:14:16.41,dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're all stored in countless drawers within your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.41,0:14:21.25,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Kagedama takes away entire drawers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.59,0:14:24.80,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter how interested you are in any of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:27.51,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems almost random.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.01,0:14:34.01,dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, there's one area of memories\Nthat remains untouched.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.89,0:14:40.31,dialogue,,0,0,0,,The things you do, see and think every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.69,0:14:46.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cooking, weaving, your son,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.57,0:14:50.70,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and your husband, whom you see in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.20,0:14:58.12,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It might be that the Kagedama are\Nleaving the everyday things for last
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.75,0:15:00.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,in order to keep their host alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.04,0:15:05.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, are you saying I wouldn't forget those things?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.80,0:15:08.51,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's just my guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.05,0:15:12.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it could be that once you've got few memories left,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.51,0:15:17.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,those remaining memories will be consumed as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.81,0:15:20.77,dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are only two things that I can recommend.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.77,0:15:23.77,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Learn as many new things as you can,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.15,0:15:28.94,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and repeatedly recall the things\Nthat you don't want to forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.53,0:15:35.53,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand. I will do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.74,0:15:36.95,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.29,0:15:41.08,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't just wait at home.\NYou should go out more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.04,0:15:44.63,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right. I think I'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.96,0:15:48.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,How 'bout we go find Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.42,0:15:52.59,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you look so silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.76,0:15:56.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've always been thinking of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.60,0:16:02.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I was afraid of finding out what happened to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.10,0:16:06.11,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm tired of waiting though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.36,0:16:07.57,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.94,0:16:11.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad often talked about the city to the west.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.07,0:16:14.45,dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about we try there first?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.20,0:16:16.62,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is she going to be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.03,0:16:21.12,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll come with me, right, Kaji?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.79,0:16:26.88,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.84,0:16:34.13,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.43,0:16:36.64,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.43,0:16:38.97,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.47,0:16:41.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, be well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.94,0:16:46.98,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure that was the best thing for them to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.78,0:16:56.28,dialogue,,0,0,0,,A year passed until I saw them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.33,0:17:03.58,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.50,0:17:06.79,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ginko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.33,0:17:08.79,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.78,0:17:12.32,sign,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\frz4.706\pos(338,550)}Tea  Shop
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.09,0:17:10.25,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.84,0:17:12.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.80,0:17:15.51,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like your mom's doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.93,0:17:16.80,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.30,0:17:18.97,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you get to meet your dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.35,0:17:21.31,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.06,0:17:23.77,dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was in the town to the west.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.14,0:17:27.40,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Living with another family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.57,0:17:31.19,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. I know them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.07,0:17:33.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try that house over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.00,0:17:44.79,dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.37,0:17:46.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.09,0:17:55.17,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom! Why aren't you saying anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.09,0:17:58.30,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.22,0:18:06.31,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom walked in silence for the entire trip home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.69,0:18:10.81,dialogue,,0,0,0,,She'd neither eat nor sleep, and eventually...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.78,0:18:13.57,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.23,0:18:15.03,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.24,0:18:18.74,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.96,0:18:30.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,She must have been tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.54,0:18:36.92,dialogue,,0,0,0,,She slept for days.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.57,0:18:58.07,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.14,0:19:25.01,dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Something just went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.10,0:19:30.14,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.81,0:19:34.15,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with that look?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.16,0:19:44.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I slept so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.37,0:19:47.62,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, time for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.29,0:19:51.50,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.50,0:19:53.75,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:58.76,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are we here again?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.26,0:20:04.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were coming home from hiking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.01,0:20:06.43,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.10,0:20:11.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.10,0:20:13.44,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.15,0:20:15.73,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just eat something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.82,0:20:19.28,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's do that, I'm starving.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.53,0:20:24.49,dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.03,0:20:27.03,dialogue,,0,0,0,,let's hurry...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.83,0:20:32.29,dialogue,,0,0,0,,and go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.33,0:20:43.55,dialogue,,0,0,0,,That morning, Mom had forgotten everything
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.09,0:20:48.93,dialogue,,0,0,0,,except about me, about home, and a few close things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.64,0:20:58.11,dialogue,,0,0,0,,She must have had most of her memories\Nconsumed when she shut herself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.73,0:21:07.28,dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she still remembers about me\Nand about how to cook and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.08,0:21:14.33,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must be because we go outside every day\Nto see new things like you told us to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.17,0:21:17.96,dialogue,,0,0,0,,She forgets most of it by the next day,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.84,0:21:22.34,dialogue,,0,0,0,,but she's enjoying it every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.17,0:21:25.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does she still not sleep at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.18,0:21:30.35,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she still weaves all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.64,0:21:32.47,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.23,0:21:34.85,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same old, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.27,0:21:35.98,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.27,0:21:39.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same old.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.61,0:21:44.86,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.40,0:21:46.57,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.03,0:21:50.08,dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost dinner; go wash your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.08,0:21:50.78,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.12,0:22:00.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom, that's one too many servings again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.38,0:22:06.09,dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right. There's only the two of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.13,0:22:11.60,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder why I thought to do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.56,0:22:18.27,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel better when I do this though.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.90,0:22:21.23,dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder why.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.03,0:22:25.99,dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why was it again?
